      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ACHY BREAKY (8) showed enough in her first two runs earlier this year where she jumped favourite before the break. Her latest trial was very impressive at Ascot and Chris Parnham sticks from that recent trial. Looks ready to fire on resumption. ACE QUEEN SUITED (6) is another who has trialled well coming into her resuming effort, winning her latest heat at Ascot. She jumped favourite ahead of a smart type two back before a good effort from the back at Pinjarra most recently. Can put her best foot forward. LUNA WILL DO (10) gets Pike in the saddle for her second-up effort after closing nicely first-up. Should be better for that effort and a slightly better draw this time helps. Can feature in the finish. LEVATI DIMEZZO (2) beat home LUNA WILL DO last time out and makes plenty of appeal again. MYSTIC SMILE (7) draws well again today and with that run under her belt, she can turn in an improved effort.",
